      "amount": "1/4 tsp",
      "notes": "food-grade, organic"
    },
    {
      "name": "pandan extract",
      "amount": "1/2 tsp",
      "notes": "plant-based, low-carb, natural sweetener-free"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 425°f (220°c) with a wood fire or conventional heat.",
    "add the dasima sheets to a hot stone plate and toast lightly for 2-3 minutes to remove moisture.",
    "in a separate mixing bowl, combine the coconut milk, lightly beaten eggs, turmeric powder, paprika, salt, and caramel color powder. Mix well to combine.",
    "pour the wet mixture over the toasted dasima sheets on the hot stone plate.",
    "bake for an additional 12-15 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the eggs are cooked through, and the dasima is tender.",
    "remove from heat and let cool for 2-3 minutes before serving."
  ],
